g the mode of a small sample. We generalize this result to the\nmultivalued case by providing a new analytical proof for the bivalued case that\nis amenable to be extended, by induction, and that is of independent interest.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Jul 2015 12:02:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Jul 2015 00:59:08 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 17 Aug 2015 12:20:07 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 14 Feb 2016 03:21:06 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 22 May 2016 10:28:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-24"}
